cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use CausalAtlas, please cite it as below."
title: "CausalAtlas: where causal grounding lives in LLM-orchestrated perturbation foundation models"
authors:
  - family-names: Kim
    given-names: JangKeun
version: 0.1.2
date-released: 2026-06-16
license: Apache-2.0
abstract: >
  A measurement-first study of causal grounding when a large language model orchestrates a fallible single-cell
  perturbation foundation model. Across five settings on real data (Norman 2019 / GEARS, Replogle, Tahoe / Arc
  STATE) and real frontier LLMs, the binding constraint is shown to be the quality of the per-input
  competence/value signal -- mean-dominated and weak by default, but engineerable to near-oracle -- rather than
  model scale, agent capability, or naive reinforcement learning.
